title: Pisano Factors
text: Given an integer n.Find how many integers c are there such that their Pisano period is a factor of n.1 ≤ c ≤ 105There are multiple test cases.InputThe first line contains number of test cases, 1 ≤ t ≤ 100Next t lines contain an integer n each. 1 ≤ n ≤ 109OutputOutput the answer to each test case on a separate line.ExampleInput:36910Output:322
